Faulu Microfinance Bank has named Equity Bank Uganda acting managing director Apollo Njoroge its new chief executive. He takes over from Charles Njuguna who has been at the helm of the country&rsquo;s second largest micro-lender for three years. Faulu said it is banking on Njoroge&rsquo;s experience to keep the lender, owned by UAP-Old Mutual Group, ona growth trajectory. &ldquo;Njoroge is an experienced financial executive with over 24 years&rsquo; experience in retail, micro, small and medium enterprises banking across East Africa,&rdquo; it said in a statement. Njoroge has also served at the African Banking Corporation and I&amp;M Bank.